===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|geomorphology}} A slope or inclination of the earth, as the side of a hill, considered as ''ascending'', in opposition to ''[[declivity]]'', or ''descending''; an upward slope; [[ascent]].
#* {{RQ:Grey Riders|8}}
#*: Just below it leaned a tottering crag that would have toppled, starting an avalanche on an '''acclivity''' where no sliding mass could stop.

